## 🛠️ The "Big Brain" Strategy: "Ghost of the Player"
Imagine playing the Russia campaign and seeing a specific burned-out **Compliance Bus** in the exact spot *you* parked it during your Regency run three weeks ago.
 * **Godot/Supabase Implementation:** When a mission ends, you save the Vector3 coordinates and Asset_ID of every destroyed unit to Supabase.
 * **The Load:** When the Russia campaign starts a mission on that map, it pulls those coordinates and spawns "Wreckage" meshes in those exact spots.
**This makes the game feel like a living history book.** You aren't just playing levels; you're witnessing the fall of a superpower from three different angles.
